2 compartments PK

mod <- mread("pk2", modlib())
## Building pk2 ... done.
print(see(mod))
## 
## Model file:  pk2.cpp 
## $PARAM @annotated
## CL   :  1 : Clearance (volume/time)
## V2   : 20 : Central volume (volume)
## Q    :  2 : Inter-compartmental clearance (volume/time)
## V3   : 10 : Peripheral volume of distribution (volume)
## KA   :  1 : Absorption rate constant (1/time)
## 
## $CMT @annotated
## EV     : Extravascular compartment (mass)
## CENT   : Central compartment (mass)
## PERIPH : Peripheral compartment (mass) 
## 
## $GLOBAL
## #define CP (CENT/V2)
## 
## $PKMODEL ncmt = 2, depot = TRUE
## 
## $CAPTURE @annotated
## CP : Plasma concentration (mass/time)
##   
## NULL
print(param(mod))
## 
##  Model parameters (N=5):
##  name value . name value
##  CL   1     | V2   20   
##  KA   1     | V3   10   
##  Q    2     | .    .
mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot()

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot()

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4) %>%
  Req(EV, CP) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot()

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4, cmt=2, rate=8) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot()

mod <- mread("pk2", modlib())
## Building pk2 ... (waiting) ...
## done.
idata <- expand.idata(V2 = c(10, 30, 70))
idata
param(mod)
## 
##  Model parameters (N=5):
##  name value . name value
##  CL   1     | V2   20   
##  KA   1     | V3   10   
##  Q    2     | .    .
mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4) %>%
  idata_set(idata) %>%
  Req(CP) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot() 

idata <- expand.idata(V2 = c(10, 30, 70),
                      CL = c(0.5, 1))
idata
mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4) %>%
  idata_set(idata) %>%
  Req(CP) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot() 

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100, ii=20, addl=4) %>%
  idata_set(idata) %>%
  Req(CP) %>%
  carry_out(V2, CL) %>%
  mrgsim(delta = 0.1, end=200) %>%
  plot(CP ~ time | factor(CL), scales="same")

Random effects

mod <- mread("popex", getwd()) 
## Building popex ... done.
see(mod)
## 
## Model file:  popex.cpp 
## $PROB
## # Example population PK model
## 
## $PARAM TVKA = 2.5, TVQ = 10, TVCL = 1, TVV2 = 50, TVV3 = 110
## 
## $PARAM @covariates
## WT = 70
## 
## $PKMODEL cmt="GUT CENT PERI", depot=TRUE
## 
## $SET end=80, delta=0.5
## 
## $MAIN
## double CL = exp(log(TVCL) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ECL);
## double Q = exp(log(TVQ) + 0.75*log(WT/70) + ECQ);
## double V2  = exp(log(TVV2)  +      log(WT/70) + EV2 );
## double V3  = exp(log(TVV3)  +      log(WT/70) + EV3 );
## double KA = exp(log(TVKA)                   + EKA);
## 
## $OMEGA @labels ECL ECQ EV2 EV3 EKA
## 0.3 0.1 0.1 0.4 0.1
## 
## $SIGMA 0
## 
## $TABLE
## capture IPRED = CENT/V3;
## capture DV = IPRED*exp(EPS(1));
## 
## $CAPTURE CL Q V2 V3 KA ECL
## 
## 
param(mod)
## 
##  Model parameters (N=6):
##  name value . name value
##  TVCL 1     | TVV2 50   
##  TVKA 2.5   | TVV3 110  
##  TVQ  10    | WT   70
idata <- expand.idata(WT = runif(100, 40, 140))

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100) %>% 
  idata_set(idata) %>%
  mrgsim(end=48, delta=0.1)

Without random effects just the influence of the weight

mod %>% 
  ev(amt=100) %>% 
  idata_set(idata) %>%
  zero_re() %>%
  mrgsim(end=48, delta=0.1) %>%
  plot(DV~time)

data <- expand.ev(ID = 1:15, amt=c(250, 500)) %>% mutate(dose=amt)

data <- mutate(data, WT = runif(n(), 50, 130))

mod %>%
  data_set(data) %>%
  Req(DV) %>%
  carry_out(dose) %>%
  zero_re() %>%
  mrgsim(end=72, delta=0.1) %>%
  plot(DV ~ time | factor(dose), scales="same")

With the random effects

mod %>%
  data_set(data) %>%
  Req(DV) %>%
  carry_out(dose) %>%
  mrgsim(end=72, delta=0.1) %>%
  plot(DV ~ time | factor(dose), scales="same")

data("exTheoph")
head(exTheoph)
mod %>%
  data_set(exTheoph) %>%
  mrgsim() %>%
  plot(DV~time, type='b')

mod %>%
  data_set(exTheoph, evid==1) %>%
  mrgsim() %>%
  plot(DV~time, type='b')
